<p>Sources of co2</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>1. Land use change - Jhum cultivation, deforestation for cultivation (5gtco2)</p>
<p>2. Cattle methane</p>
<p>4. Farm machinery on fossil fuel</p>
<p>3. Food wastage too (8%)</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Emission reduction strategy&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>1. Food production - alternative de carbonised food production</p>
<p>2. Electricity</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Howto decarbonise food ?&nbsp;</p>
<p>1. Food supply chain</p>
<p>2. Food production practices need to change e.g. lab grown meat</p>
<p>3. Food wastage reduce (8% GHG)</p>
<p>4. Diet change - shift to plant based diet (60%) reduce ghg as per EAT-LANCET report.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Way forward</p>
<p>Increasing 10bn people eating in planetary boundaries needs consistent and immediate effort.</p>